amns_data.documentation: Atomic, molecular, nuclear and surface physics data. Each occurrence contains the data for a given element (nuclear charge), describing various physical processes. For each process, data tables are organized by charge states. The coordinate system used by the data tables is described under the coordinate_system node.

amns_data.a_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "a"

amns_data.code.documentation: Generic decription of the code-specific parameters for the code that has produced this IDS

amns_data.code.output_flag.documentation: Output flag : 0 means the run is successful, other values mean some difficulty has been encountered, the exact meaning is then code specific. Negative values mean the result shall not be used.

amns_data.code.parameters.documentation: List of the code specific parameters in XML format

amns_data.coordinate_system.documentation: Array of possible coordinate systems for process tables

amns_data.coordinate_system[:].coordinat.documentation: Set of coordinates for that coordinate system. A coordinate an be either a range of real values or a set of discrete values (if interpolation_type=0)

Extrapolation strategy when leaving the domain. The first value of the vector describes the behaviour at lower bound, the second describes the at upper bound. Possible values: 0=none, report error; 1=boundary value; 2=linear extrapolation
Interpolation strategy in this coordinate direction. Integer flag: 0=discrete (no interpolation); 1=linear; ...
Flag for specific coordinate spacing (for optimization purposes). Integer flag: 0=undefined; 1=uniform; ...
Coordinate transformation applied to coordinate values stored in coord. Integer flag: 0=none; 1=log10; 2=ln
String description of discrete coordinate values (if interpolation_type=0). E.g., for spectroscopic lines, the spectroscopic description of the transition.
Index in the error_description list for "values"

amns_data.ids_properties.documentation: Interface Data Structure properties. This element identifies the node above as an IDS

amns_data.ids_properties.comment.documentation: Any comment describing the content of this IDS

amns_data.ids_properties.creation_date.documentation: Date at which this data has been produced

amns_data.ids_properties.homogeneous_tim.documentation: This node must be filled (with 0 or 1) for the IDS to be valid. If 1, the time of this IDS is homogeneous, i.e. the time values for this IDS are stored in the time node just below the root of this IDS. If 0, the time values are stored in the various time fields at lower levels in the tree. In the case only constant or static nodes are filled within the IDS, this node must still be filled, and set to 1 (by convention).

amns_data.ids_properties.provider.documentation: Name of the person in charge of producing this data

amns_data.ids_properties.source.documentation: Source of the data (any comment describing the origin of the data : code, path to diagnostic signals, processing method, ...)

amns_data.process.documentation: Description and data for a set of physical processes.

amns_data.process[:].charge_state.documentation: Process tables for a set of charge states. Only one table is used for that process, defined by process(:)/table_dimension

amns_data.process[:].charge_state[:].lab.documentation: String identifying charge state (e.g. C+, C+2 , C+3, C+4, C+5, C+6, ...)

amns_data.process[:].charge_state[:].tab.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "table_0d"
Index in the error_description list for "table_1d"
Index in the error_description list for "table_2d"
Index in the error_description list for "table_3d"
Index in the error_description list for "table_4d"
Index in the error_description list for "table_5d"
Index in the error_description list for "table_6d"

amns_data.process[:].charge_state[:].z_m.documentation: Maximum Z of the charge state bundle (equal to z_min if no bundle)
Index in the error_description list for "z_max"
Minimum Z of the charge state bundle
Index in the error_description list for "z_min"

amns_data.process[:].coordinate_index.documentation: Index in tables_coord, specifying what coordinate systems to use for this process (valid for all tables)

amns_data.process[:].label.documentation: String identifying the process (e.g. EI, RC, ...)

amns_data.process[:].products.documentation: Set of products resulting of this process

amns_data.process[:].products[:].charge_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "charge"

amns_data.process[:].products[:].element.documentation: List of elements forming the atom (in such cas, this array should be of size 1) or molecule
Number of nucleons in the nucleus (nuclear mass); 0 if none (e-, gamma); Not set if not important (e.g. for an atomic process that is not isotope dependent)
Multiplicity of the atom in the molecule
Index in the error_description list for "multiplicity"

amns_data.process[:].products[:].mass_er.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "mass"

amns_data.process[:].products[:].metasta.documentation: An array identifying the metastable; if zero-length, then not a metastable; if of length 1, then the value indicates the electronic level for the metastable (mostly used for atoms/ions); if of length 2, then the 1st would indicate the electronic level and the second the vibrational level for the metastable (mostly used for molecules and molecular ions); if of length 3, then the 1st would indicate the electronic level, the second the vibrational level and the third the rotational level for the metastable (mostly used for molecules and molecular ions)
Label identifying in text form the metastable

amns_data.process[:].products[:].multipl.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "multiplicity"

amns_data.process[:].products[:].relativ.documentation: This is a flag indicating that charges are absolute (if set to 0), relative (if 1) or irrelevant (-1); relative would be used to categorize the ionization reactions from i to i+1 for all charge states; in the case of bundles, the +1 relative indicates the next bundle

amns_data.process[:].products[:].role.documentation: Identifier for the role of this paricipant in the reaction. For surface reactions distinguish between projectile and wall.

amns_data.process[:].products[:].role.in.documentation: Integer identifier (enumeration index within a list). Private identifier values must be indicated by a negative index.

amns_data.process[:].provider.documentation: Name of the person in charge of producing this data

amns_data.process[:].reactants.documentation: Set of reactants involved in this process

amns_data.process[:].reactants[:].charge.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "charge"

amns_data.process[:].reactants[:].elemen.documentation: List of elements forming the atom (in such cas, this array should be of size 1) or molecule
Number of nucleons in the nucleus (nuclear mass); 0 if none (e-, gamma); Not set if not important (e.g. for an atomic process that is not isotope dependent)
Multiplicity of the atom in the molecule
Index in the error_description list for "multiplicity"

amns_data.process[:].reactants[:].mass_e.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "mass"

amns_data.process[:].reactants[:].metast.documentation: An array identifying the metastable; if zero-length, then not a metastable; if of length 1, then the value indicates the electronic level for the metastable (mostly used for atoms/ions); if of length 2, then the 1st would indicate the electronic level and the second the vibrational level for the metastable (mostly used for molecules and molecular ions); if of length 3, then the 1st would indicate the electronic level, the second the vibrational level and the third the rotational level for the metastable (mostly used for molecules and molecular ions)
Label identifying in text form the metastable

amns_data.process[:].reactants[:].multip.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "multiplicity"

amns_data.process[:].reactants[:].relati.documentation: This is a flag indicating that charges are absolute (if set to 0), relative (if 1) or irrelevant (-1); relative would be used to categorize the ionization reactions from i to i+1 for all charge states; in the case of bundles, the +1 relative indicates the next bundle

amns_data.process[:].reactants[:].role.documentation: Identifier for the role of this paricipant in the reaction. For surface reactions distinguish between projectile and wall.

amns_data.process[:].reactants[:].role.i.documentation: Integer identifier (enumeration index within a list). Private identifier values must be indicated by a negative index.

amns_data.process[:].result_label.documentation: Description of the process result (rate, cross section, sputtering yield, ...)

amns_data.process[:].result_transformati.documentation: Transformation of the process result. Integer flag: 0=no transformation; 1=10^; 2=exp()

amns_data.process[:].source.documentation: Filename or subroutine name used to provide this data

amns_data.process[:].table_dimension.documentation: Table dimensionality of the process (1 to 6), valid for all charge states. Indicates which of the tables is filled (below the charge_state node)

amns_data.release.documentation: List of available releases of the AMNS data; each element contains information about the AMNS data that is included in the release. This part of the IDS is filled and stored only into shot/run=0/1, playing the role of a catalogue.

amns_data.release[:].data_entry.documentation: For this release, list of each data item (i.e. shot/run pair containing the actual data) included in this release

amns_data.release[:].data_entry[:].run.documentation: Which run number is the active run number for this version

amns_data.z_n_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "z_n"
